<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7816> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7816" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.449, and Index, 604, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.436, no. 43,4, 54 B.C. He is almost certainly the tribune of the plebs of 52 B.C.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5331> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5331" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A supporter of Clodius, who was prominent in the disorders after his death (Ascon. 32-52 C, passim; Dio 40.45, and 49; cf. Cic. Mil. 45 and 47 and 90-91). Immediately after his year of office Caelius prosecuted him and sent him into exile (Val. Max. 4.2.7; Dio 40.55; cf. Cael. in Cic. Fam. 8.1.4). See D.-G. 4.319f., no. 7." .
